article.headline: W. Illinois 75, Eureka 57
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- David Dubois had 17 points and Quenton Kirby added 14 points and 10 rebounds to lead Western Illinois to a 75-57 win over Eureka on Wednesday night. Tommie Tyler scored 13 points and Josh Rivers added 10 points for Western Illinois (1-2), which led 43-38 at halftime. Shooting for Eureka (0-1) dried up in the second half, dipping to 34 percent after the break from 54 percent before. The Red Devils also sank 9-of-12 3-point shots before intermission, but just 1-of-8 after halftime. The Leathernecks outscored Eureka 15-5 from the foul line. Western Illinois shot from the line 19 times in the second half, compared to twice for the Red Devils. Michael Zasada led Eureka (0-1) with 15 points. Mark Darnall chipped in 14 points for the Red Devils.
